The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Rollout rush propels Bharti profit
                                                                                                               Rollout rush propels Bharti profit
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                          Mittal: Good show                                  
	New Delhi, Jan. 22: Bharti Airtel has posted a 38.35 per cent rise in consolidated net profit at Rs 1,976.41 crore for the third quarter ended December 31, 2008, on the back of a smart increase in the subscriber base.         
	Bharti added a record 82 lakh users during the quarter, taking its total users to 857 lakh.        
	According to Indian accounting rules, net profit for the quarter under review rose to Rs 1,976.41 crore from Rs 1,428.56 crore a year ago.        
	Total income increased 38 per cent to Rs 9,688.50 crore from Rs 7,017.95 crore. For the nine months ended December 31, Bharti posted a net profit of Rs 5,811.22 crore, up 29.23 per cent from Rs 4,496.53 crore in the year-ago period.         
	Bhartis strategy of extensive rollout ahead of competition, especially in new villages, has yielded rich dividends, said Sunil Mittal, chairman of the company. Bharti Airtel is well placed to capitalise on the huge telecom opportunity that India offers, he said.        
	According to US accounting rules, Airtel registered a 25 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 2,159 crore for the reporting quarter against Rs 1,722 crore a year ago.         
	Revenue grew 38 per cent to Rs 9,633 crore from Rs 6,964 crore.         
	The New Delhi-based telecom player has earmarked around Rs 24,000 crore for capital expenditure.         
	About Rs 12,000 crore has been earmarked for mobile services and approximately Rs 14,000 crore for passive infrastructure, said Akhil Gupta, deputy chief executive of the Bharti group.         
	Passive infrastructure is the companys tower business run by Bharti Infratel and Indus Towers  an independent tower entity formed by Bharti, Vodafone and Idea.                                                                                                                                        
